== Notable Individuals == The following individuals held the Rank of Shōkinchū, as recorded in the [[:en:Nihon Shoki|Nihon Shoki]]: * {{ill|Kawachi Kujira|ja|河内鯨|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kawachi Kujira|qq=}} - Recognized in the 8th year of Emperor Tenji's reign (669) as an envoy to Tang China.<ref>{{nihonshoki|Tenji|8|}}.</ref> * {{ill|Maishin no Oogai|ja|間人大蓋|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Maishin no Oogai|qq=}} - Conducted rituals at the Hirose River in the 4th year of Emperor Tenmu's reign (675). * {{ill|Inabe no Shikō|ja|忌部子首|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Inabe no Shikō|qq=}} - Tasked with recording imperial genealogies and ancient affairs in the 10th year of Emperor Tenmu's reign (681).<ref>{{nihonshoki|Tenmu|10|3|17}}.</ref> * {{ill|Otomo no Otomaro|ja|大伴安麻呂|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōtomo no Yasumaro|qq=}} - Surveyed the Kinai region for suitable capital sites in the 13th year of Emperor Tenmu's reign (684).<ref>{{nihonshoki|Tenmu|13|2|28}}.</ref>
